The cam made the plane a little tail-heavy, and it made flight feel a little wobbly so I decided to lay off the stunts.  (Or should I say stunt?  this thing can only do loops as far as I know.)

The song is "Eer Amak Et'Amorve!" (1998) by Keith303.  You can download it at http://keith303.bandcamp.com/track/eer-amak-et-amorve-1998, or in the original .XM format from his homepage at http://www.keith303.de/ (used under Creative Commons license, http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/3.0/legalcode )

4MbLnt2Vvbw.title: SPANDAN 2013 Dance 8 Nitisha Nanda - Classical Belly Dance
4MbLnt2Vvbw.description:
Nitisha has been training in Oidssi at Pratidhwani as a disciple of Guru Ipsita Behoora (student of Late Shri Kelucharan Mohapatra) and Sri Samir Kumar Behra for the past 7 years. Nitisha has been formerly trained under Guru Hare Krishna Behera.  She has been dancing for the past 17 years now. 
Besides classical Odissi, Nitisha is also a trained Belly Dancer, working with the Banjara School of Dance as an instructor and performer and training under Meher Malik. Apart from this, she has also received training in Contemporary, Bollywood and Salsa. 

She has travelled around India to various places like Mumbai, Jodhpur, Hyderabad, Goa, to name a few, for various shows and also to Cairo, Egypt for the Nile Festival. She has also been a part of popular television shows like Just Dance, India's Got Talent, Entertainment Ke Liye Kuch Bhi Karega and performed with Rani Mukherjee in a song of her latest movie "Aiyya".

Belly Dance - Drum solo
Like in Indian classical dance, there are multiple pieces that are performed and learnt, in a belly dance repertoire, the Drum Solo is something which falls in the latter half. This drum solo, being performed today, is a combination of various rhythms like-Balaedi, Saidi, Khaleeji, Felahi and Ayub belonging to both Egypt and the Gulf. All these folk rhythms have been adapted in Raqs Sharqi stylization of dance, that is the classical Egyptian style. Music is by Mario Kirlis.

UURZ0_wuPDo.title: My mountain bike after fateful meeting with truck (aka "I will let the bike shop determine that").
UURZ0_wuPDo.description:
This is my Diamondback full suspension mountain bike. It is not the best bike out there, but it suits me just fine for now. Yesterday; October 7, 2010 it got ran over by a truck while on a bike path. The fellow has agreed to pay the repair costs, which right now stand at $265. The bike was purchased brand new for about $700.

This is the video I took of my bike before I brought it to one of the local bike repair shops to document the damage should the fellow decide not to follow up on his word.

When he ran over my bike, he smashed the back end,  and stayed on it, which dug the whole bike into the ground. If your bike gets run over, or you have a bad wreck on it take it in for repairs. Some types of damage to bikes... especially frame and rim/hub damage can cause fatal accidents down the road. Its not worth saving a few hundred on repairs only to have a very serious and probably even MORE expensive mishap down the road.

Its fun to live on the edge, but it's more fun to be alive to do such things!

Moonshine:
Take one part soul-soaked soaring female vocals, one part blues-infused rock guitar, add a dash of New Orleans jazz horns, sprinkle with funky bass, and shake it up with internationally acclaimed musicians.  Meet Moonshine- the perfect band for the most discerning music lovers.  Called "The Musician's Band", Moonshine is the ultimate in high level performance and fun, party music.  Comprised of Berklee College of Music alumni, with multiple members of the Blues Hall of Fame, the 7 piece band brings a punch of flavor  to every event they're a part of.  

Moonshine strives to keep the dance floor full with a variety of great music, ranging from Motown, Blues, Classic and Southern Rock, Top 40, 80's classics, and Jazz.  No synthesized sounds, no backing tracks, no auto-tune- everything the band plays is live, including the Hammond B3 sounds coming from the key's Leslie cabinet.  

The band has had the pleasure of performing at Inaugural Balls, college events, festivals, weddings, corporate parties, casinos, and night clubs, thrilling audiences coast to coast and internationally.  Perfect for events that want something "a little different" than your typical wedding band, Moonshine Society brings class and sass all in one fun package. 

Jazz trio available for cocktail/dinner hours.  Solo guitarist or pianist available for ceremonies.    A truly memorable event calls for a truly great live band.  Look no further than Moonshine.
